frameworks.name: Data Management Body of Knowledge (BMBOK)
frameworks.description: Data management framework for data governance created by the Data Management Association (DAMA International).

frameworks.name: Data Management Capabilities Assessment Model 2.2 (DCAM 2.2)
frameworks.description: The DCAM framework was created by the EDM Council formed by the Global Financial Industry and assesses current data management capabilities using a scoring model.

frameworks.name: Control Objectives for Information and Related Technologies (COBIT)
frameworks.description: Data management framework for data governance created by Information Systems Audit and Control Association (ISACA).

frameworks.name: Data Management Maturity (DMM) Model
frameworks.description: Data management framework with maturity levels for data governance created by Carnegie Mellon Universiy's CMMI Institute.
